You have performed cesarean surgery.
!Activity 
1. Have changing stations and feeding supplies close to you so that you do not have to get up too often.
2. Get plenty of rest.
3. Be alert to any fever or pain, which can both be signs of infection.
4. You may resume your sexual life a week or two after the surgery.
5. In addition to pain medicine, you can use a heating pad to relieve discomfort at the surgical site.@
%Diet care
1. You need extra fluids to boost your breast milk supply and to avoid constipation.
2. Eat healthy meals to restore your energy and prevent constipation.
